    "surah_info": {
        "surah_name": "Surah At-Takwir",
        "ayah_count": "29",
        "revelation_place": "Mecca",
        "description": "NameIt is derived from the word kuwwirat in the first verse. Kuwwirat is passive voice from takwir in the past tense, and means \"that which is folded up\", thereby implying that it is a Surah in which the \"folding up\" has been mentioned:Period of RevelationThe subject matter and the style clearly show that it is one of the earliest Surahs to be revealed at Makkah.Theme and Subject MatterIt has two themes: the Hereafter and the institution of Prophethood.In the first six verses, the first stage of the Resurrection has been mentioned when the sun will lose its light, the stars will scatter, the mountains will be uprooted and will disperse, the people will become heedless of their dearest possessions, the beasts of the jungle will be stupefied and will gather together, and the seas will boil up. Then in the next seven verses, the second stage has been described when the souls will be reunited with the bodies, the records will be laid open, the people will be called to account for their crimes, the heavens will be unveiled, and Hell and Heaven will be brought into full view. After depicting the Hereafter thus, man has been left to ponder his own self and deeds, saying: \"Then each man shall himself know what he has brought with him.\"After this, the theme of Prophethood has been taken up. In this the people of Makkah have been addressed, as if to say \"Whatever Muhammad (upon whom be Allah's peace and blessings) is presenting before you, is not the bragging of a madman, nor an evil suggestion inspired by Satan, but the word of a noble, exalted and trustworthy messenger sent by God, whom Muhammad (upon whom be Allah's peace and blessings) has seen with his own eyes in the bright horizon of the clear sky in broad daylight. Whither then are you going having turned away from this teaching?\""
    },
    "surah_verses": [
        {
            "verse_key": "81:1",
            "verse_num": "81:1",
            "arabic_text": " إِذَا ٱلشَّمْسُ كُوِّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "When the sun is put out,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:2",
            "verse_num": "81:2",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلنُّجُومُ ٱنكَدَرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the stars fall down,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:3",
            "verse_num": "81:3",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْجِبَالُ سُيِّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the mountains are blown away,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:4",
            "verse_num": "81:4",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْعِشَارُ عُطِّلَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when pregnant camels are left untended,<sup foot_note=77595>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:5",
            "verse_num": "81:5",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْوُحُوشُ حُشِرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when wild beasts are gathered together,<sup foot_note=77596>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:6",
            "verse_num": "81:6",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْبِحَارُ سُجِّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the seas are set on fire,<sup foot_note=77597>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:7",
            "verse_num": "81:7",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلنُّفُوسُ زُوِّجَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the souls ˹and their bodies˺ are paired ˹once more˺,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:8",
            "verse_num": "81:8",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْمَوْءُۥدَةُ سُئِلَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when baby girls, buried alive, are asked"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:9",
            "verse_num": "81:9",
            "arabic_text": "بِأَىِّ ذَنۢبٍ قُتِلَتْ",
            "en_text": "for what crime they were put to death,<sup foot_note=77598>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:10",
            "verse_num": "81:10",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلصُّحُفُ نُشِرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the records ˹of deeds˺ are laid open,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:11",
            "verse_num": "81:11",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلسَّمَآءُ كُشِطَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the sky is stripped away,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:12",
            "verse_num": "81:12",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْجَحِيمُ سُعِّرَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when the Hellfire is fiercely flared up,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:13",
            "verse_num": "81:13",
            "arabic_text": "وَإِذَا ٱلْجَنَّةُ أُزْلِفَتْ",
            "en_text": "and when Paradise is brought near—"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:14",
            "verse_num": "81:14",
            "arabic_text": "عَلِمَتْ نَفْسٌ مَّآ أَحْضَرَتْ",
            "en_text": "˹on that Day˺ each soul will know what ˹deeds˺ it has brought along."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:15",
            "verse_num": "81:15",
            "arabic_text": "فَلَآ أُقْسِمُ بِٱلْخُنَّسِ",
            "en_text": "I do swear by the receding stars"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:16",
            "verse_num": "81:16",
            "arabic_text": "ٱلْجَوَارِ ٱلْكُنَّسِ",
            "en_text": "which travel and hide,<sup foot_note=77599>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:17",
            "verse_num": "81:17",
            "arabic_text": "وَٱلَّيْلِ إِذَا عَسْعَسَ",
            "en_text": "and the night as it falls"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:18",
            "verse_num": "81:18",
            "arabic_text": "وَٱلصُّبْحِ إِذَا تَنَفَّسَ",
            "en_text": "and the day as it breaks!<sup foot_note=77600>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:19",
            "verse_num": "81:19",
            "arabic_text": "إِنَّهُۥ لَقَوْلُ رَسُولٍ كَرِيمٍ",
            "en_text": "Indeed, this ˹Quran˺ is the Word of ˹Allah delivered by Gabriel,˺ a noble messenger-angel,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:20",
            "verse_num": "81:20",
            "arabic_text": "ذِى قُوَّةٍ عِندَ ذِى ٱلْعَرْشِ مَكِينٍ",
            "en_text": "full of power, held in honour by the Lord of the Throne,"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:21",
            "verse_num": "81:21",
            "arabic_text": "مُّطَاعٍ ثَمَّ أَمِينٍ",
            "en_text": "obeyed there ˹in heaven˺, and trustworthy."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:22",
            "verse_num": "81:22",
            "arabic_text": "وَمَا صَاحِبُكُم بِمَجْنُونٍ",
            "en_text": "And your fellow man<sup foot_note=77601>1</sup> is not insane."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:23",
            "verse_num": "81:23",
            "arabic_text": "وَلَقَدْ رَءَاهُ بِٱلْأُفُقِ ٱلْمُبِينِ",
            "en_text": "And he did see that ˹angel˺ on the clear horizon,<sup foot_note=77602>1</sup>"
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:24",
            "verse_num": "81:24",
            "arabic_text": "وَمَا هُوَ عَلَى ٱلْغَيْبِ بِضَنِينٍ",
            "en_text": "and he does not withhold ˹what is revealed to him of˺ the unseen."
        },
        {
            "verse_key": "81:25",
            "verse_num": "81:25",
